\begin_layout Subsection*
Problem 1: Crank-Nicolson
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Suppose we are discretizing a wave equation 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial\vec{w}}{\partial t}=\hat{D}\vec{w}$
\end_inset

 for an anti-Hermitian 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{D}$
\end_inset

.
 We discretize space to obtain an anti-Hermitian matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $D$
\end_inset

.
 Show that the Crank-Nicolson time discretization 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\vec{w}^{n+1}-\vec{w}^{n}}{\Delta t}=D\frac{\vec{w}^{n+1}+\vec{w}^{n}}{2}
\]

\end_inset

 is unconditionally stable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Problem 1: Schrödinger 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Suppose that you are discretizing the 1d Schrödinger wave equation (nondimension
alized and with a real potential 
\begin_inset Formula $V(x)$
\end_inset

): 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\partial u}{\partial t}=i\left[\frac{\partial^{2}u}{\partial x^{2}}+V(x)u\right].
\]

\end_inset

Suppose that we discretize in space at intervals 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta x$
\end_inset

 and in time with some timestep 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta t$
\end_inset

, denoting 
\begin_inset Formula $u(m\Delta x,n\Delta t)\approx u_{m}^{n}$
\end_inset

 as in class.
 We will discretized 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial^{2}/\partial x^{2}$
\end_inset

 with the usual center-difference approximation 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{u_{m+1}-2u_{m}+u_{m-1}}{\Delta x^{2}}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
