\end_inset

 in terms of its real part 
\begin_inset Formula $a(x,t)$
\end_inset

 and its imaginary part 
\begin_inset Formula $b(x,t)$
\end_inset

, and discretize 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 at different times (offset by 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta t/2$
\end_inset

); you should be able to write two coupled 
\emph on
real
